The Sydney teenager who speared the skull of Liam Knight with a metal pole has been sentenced to at least eight years.

Liam was one of about 70 guests celebrating the 18th birthday of his friend Harry Staples in Forestville in Sydney's north in January last year when things went horribly wrong.

The then 16-year-old known as DS gatecrashed the party with four other young men only to be told they were not on the guest list, and unwelcome.

