DS then scaled a high fence at the home and climbed onto the roof of a shed, shouting to his mates, 'come on, we can come through this way'.

Harry Staples' father, Phillip Staples, shone a torch on DS and said: 'Mate, you're not invited, you have to leave.'

Angry and intoxicated, pushed Mr Staples in the chest, and punched one of the party guests in the face. Then he began throwing building materials at partygoers.

One of four steel three-metre rebars that he threw into the crowd pierced Liam's skull and lodged in his head.

Paramedics arrived on the scene and sedated Knight, but had to wait for firefighters to cut the large piece of steel protruding from his head, before they took the young man to hospital.

In Royal North Shore Hospital, Knight underwent a five hour emergency bilateral craniectomy.

